        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="gez">
                <note>Text of the Miracles provided after <ref type="mss" target="ESamq001"/></note>
    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle1"><label>Stone that was given to the Saint turns bread</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡ <gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>
          ወእንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡ ውስተ፡ ደብር፡ ዘስሙ፡ ሐረይክዋ፡ እንዘ፡ ይትሜሀር፡ </ab></div>
                    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle2"><label>Those who stole crops from the fields of the monks are punished with death</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>
          ፪ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/> ወመጽአ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ወይቤልዎ፡ ኦአባ፡ ሠረቁ፨ እምግራህተነ፡
            </ab></div>
    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle3"><label>A man who stole cactii begs the Saint for pardon</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፫ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>
            ወኮነ፡ ብእሲ፡ ዓለማዊ፡ ግዕዘ፡ እምሀገሩ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡ በምድረ፡ ቈላቍሎ፡ ወሖረ፡ ውስተ፡ ካልእ፡ ሀገር፡ ወተመይጦ፡ ሠረቀ፡ ቈልቋል፡ ዘውስተ፡ ቤት፡</ab></div>
    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle4"><label>The Saint introduces into monastic profession the priest ʾƎndrǝyās at Bet Qirqos</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፩ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/> ወበ፩፡ ዕለት፡ ወጽአ፡ አብ፡ እማህደሩ፡ ውስተ፡ ሀገር፡ እንተ፡ ስማ፡ ቤተ፡ ቂርቆስ፡
ከመ፡ ያልብሶ፡ ለአባ፡ እንድርያስ፡ ቀሲስ፨</ab></div>

    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle5"><label>How the Saint killed a snake that sneaked into his clothes</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፭ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>
         ወእንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡ ውስተ፡ ጾማዕት፡ መጽአ፡ ከይሲ፡ ወቦአ፡ ውስተ፡ መልበሱ፡</ab></div>
    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle6"><label>The governor of Qǝfrǝyā requires tributes from the land assigned for the Saint's commemoration;
      the people entreat to the Saint; the governor gets punished</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፮ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>
      ወበ፩መጽአ፡ ደቂቁ፡ ወይቤልዎ፡ ነሥኡ፡ ገራሀተነ፡ እምደረ፡ ሰሰዊ፡</ab></div>
    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle7"><label>A story of the death of the Saint who prophesizes that King Dāwit will reign</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፯ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>
             ወኮነ፡ በ፩እመዋዕል፡ መጽአ፡ ስዩመ፡ ቅፍርያ፨ ውስተ፡ ማኅደሩ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡ </ab></div>
    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle8"><label>A demon is expelled from a man who slept at the grave of the Saint,
    in the time of King ʾƎskǝndǝr</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፰ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>ወኮነ፡ አቡነ፡
      ማማስ፡ እንዘ፡ ያንሶሱ፡ ዲበ፡ ምድር፡ እንዘ፡ ሀሎ፡ ብሕይወቱ፡ ይመጽአ፡ መካናት፡ ኀቤሁ፡ ወይትኀሠሣ፡</ab></div>
    </div>

    <div type="textpart" subtype="miracle" xml:id="Miracle9"><label>Discourse about the greatness of the Saint</label>
        <div type="textpart" subtype="incipit"><ab>፱ተአምሪሁ፡ ለአቡነ፡ ማማስ፡<gap reason="ellipsis" resp="DN"/>
        ወአመ፡ ዕለተ፡ ተዝካሩ፡ ይትጋብኡ፡ ብዙኀን፡ ሰብእ፨ በከመ፡ ይትጋብኡ፡ ኀበመቃበረ፡ ቶማስ፡ ሐዋርያ፡ በሀገረ፡ ህንዳኬ፨</ab></div>
    </div>
    </div>




